-- FCC to Sell Stake in Czech Water Unit to Mitsui for $127 Million
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2013-07-02T08:53:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-02/fcc-to-sell-stake-in-czech-water-unit-to-mitsui-for-127-million.html
Fomento de Construcciones & Contratas
SA  will sell 49 percent of its Czech water unit SmVak to  Mitsui
& Co. (8031)  to help the Spanish infrastructure company reduce debt.  The Barcelona-based company will the stake to Mitsui for 97
million euros ($127 million), it said today in a statement. FCC
will remain the controlling shareholder after the sale, which
won’t affect FCC’s results, it said in a separate statement.  SmVak is the fourth-biggest water company in the Czech
Republic and posted more than 42 million euros of earnings
before interest, tax, depreciation and amortization on sales of
108 million euros in 2012.  FCC planned 2.2 billion euros of non-strategic asset sales,
Chief Executive Officer Juan Bejar said in March. The company
agreed to sell its stake in water and waste company Proactiva
Medio Ambiente to  Veolia Environnement SA (VIE)  for $198 million.  FCC  advanced  0.1 percent to 7.317 euros by 10:18 a.m. in
Madrid trading, after gaining as much as 1.8 percent, giving the
company a market value of 931.5 million euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
